  "description": [
    "Friday 3 May 1963 Court Martial Drama Again On The Road The Naval Justice School will present its twoact courtmartial play at the I S Coast Guard Academy in New London Conn tonight CAPT Wilfred A Hearn Jus tice School Commanding Officer will introduce The General Court Martial Trial of Joseph Rios and Francis Sullivan to an expected audience of 800 The corps of ca dets of the Academy the Acade my staff and their ladies and officers from all branches of the Armed Forces in the New London area have been invited to attend The trial play was presented yesterday at the Family Theatre for all Newportarea military per sonnel and their guests Tonights performance is at the invitation of RADM Willard J Smith Academy Superintendent Since 1952 the play has been presented six times annually to Justice School students and others in the Newport area The play was presented in Washing ton D C on 11 March before the Armed Forces Reserve Joint As sembly Two Portsmouth Avenues Closed Personnel using Sprague and Freeborn Streets in Portsmouth are urged to take notice that the two streets will be closed to traf fic for about three months Information concerning"
